  "bead": {
    "id": "ddx-f9bb7327",
    "title": "Detect and repair parent-ancestor deps in bead doctor",
    "description": "PROBLEM\n`ddx bead doctor` can currently repair oversized fields and detect dangling-success beads, but it never scans for dependency edges that point back to a bead's parent chain. That leaves structural back-edges hidden until work loops wedge.\n\nROOT CAUSE\n`cli/internal/bead/doctor.go` only reports field-length overflow, and `cli/cmd/bead_doctor.go` only exposes the oversized-field and dangling-success modes. There is no stable, scriptable `parent_ancestor_in_deps` pass that enumerates offending beads or repairs them under `--fix`.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nExtend the bead doctor to scan for any dep whose target is the bead's parent or ancestor, emit a stable `parent_ancestor_in_deps` finding list, and remove only the offending edges when `--fix` is supplied. The command output must stay deterministic so shell tooling can parse it. Add a regression test named `ddx_doctor_detects_and_repairs_back_edge`.\n\nNON-SCOPE\nDo not change create-time validation, decomposition prompt text, work-loop remediation, or dispatch severity in this bead.\n\nIn-scope files:\n- cli/internal/bead/doctor.go\n- cli/internal/bead/doctor_test.go\n- cli/cmd/bead_doctor.go\n- cli/cmd/bead_doctor_test.go (new or existing command-level coverage)\n\nOut-of-scope:\n- cli/internal/bead/store.go\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go\n- cli/internal/agent/lifecycle_dispatch.go\n- docs/helix/02-design/technical-designs/TD-031-bead-state-machine.md",
    "acceptance": "1. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/bead/... -run TestBeadDoctorDetectsAndRepairsBackEdge` passes.\n2. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./cmd/... -run TestBeadDoctorDetectsAndRepairsBackEdge` passes.\n3. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/bead/... ./cmd/...` passes.\n4. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 lefthook run pre-commit` passes.",
